# Sportstensor Week 8 Update
@sportstensor・41 

## League prediction accuracies, then vs. now
8 weeks in and we've seen some spectacular improvements by our miners' prediction accuracies throughout our offered leagues. Let's have a look at what we've achieved together (follow along with our dashboard: https://dashboard.sportstensor.com/)
- MLB has undoubtedly been our most popular league with a strong base model starting things off at 55% in early July however, we've recently seen an all time high of **73%**!
- MLS didn't get a lot of love at the beginning with an accuracy of just 28.6% at launch, however some miners took it upon themselves to be the white knights of MLS and brought that number to an ATH of **60.44%**
- EPL showed us we had European miners itching to put their skills to use in the Premier League and in 4 weeks was able to hit an ATH of **60.64%**
- NFL had only just started less than two weeks ago and the amount of predictions are still below the usual threshold of 1,000 however with 100+ predictions, our top miner has currently achieved a whopping **96.15%** prediction accuracy!

We're proud to see the dedication that our miners are putting in to improve their models. We're confident that even with the new incentive mechanism coming, they will rise to the top!

## Check out our app!
It's fun to see users interacting with our app and even better when we get feedback on how to improve the beta version. If you haven't seen it yet, jump on our app and try it out by getting predictions of the coming games from each league: https://app.sportstensor.com/

## Miner FAQ of the week
### "I have 80% accuracy in my MLB predictions, why is my incentive low?"
Don't forget there are four leagues that validators are requesting predictions for so if you're 100% accurate in one, you'll still be penalized for making bad predictions for the other 3. Our suggestion is to:
1. Improve all four league models in unison to maintain a high incentive score
2. Work with other miners to form teams where you bring an optimised model to the table each and share the workload

Personally i'd love to see more of 2. 😊

## Incentive mechanism update
Simulations are done! (see attached for sneak peek). Without simulations, we aren't able to tell if the new incentive mechanism is actually going to distribute incentives properly and in the curve we want (pareto). Some final steps are being taken to make sure that this new incentive mechanism is aligned with ours and validator's expectations - it is quite a monumental change for our subnet and we want to use it to set the path for our future in the long run.

# Sportstensor Week 10 Update
@sportstensor・41 

## :yipee: The new incentive mechanism!
Sportstensor is entering a new era. We have taken our experience with building, feedback from miners, discussions amongst validators and all of the learnings in the last 10 weeks to **evolve our subnet** with an updated incentive mechanism.

**SN41 will be incentivising machine learning models to consistently discover edges over the closing line, also known as *closing edge*.**

## :slowparrot: How it works
If a miner predicts that the odds for team A at the markets close should be **1.45**, and the closing line ends up being **1.55**, the miner has discovered a positive closing edge of 10 cents. :countingmoney: 

## :huh: Why is this important?
Closing lines are considered **extremely efficient** and the most accurate prediction of an event's outcome, as they are **inferring a consensus win probability** from all available information provided by **many machine learning models weighted with money**.

Consistently beating the closing line at the time of market close indicates you're **identifying unique value** that the market has not factored in, beating out **hundreds if not thousands of algorithms** and is seen as a strong predictor of long-term profitability in sports betting.

:hiddenfire: **We call this *true intelligence*.** :hiddenfire: 

## :stonks: Closing Edge vs. CLV
Closing edge is when a prediction has bested the market at a point where information is maximally factored into the odds (minimum entropy). Closing line value measures how much better (or worse) the odds you got are compared to the closing odds at a time where information entropy is not minimized.

If I was to put this in to an analogy:
- Closing edge is if you defeated the final boss in a game. :quoose: 
- CLV is if you defeated an enemy but you have to keep going and you might die along the way to the final boss.

## :headshake: What we see in the near future 
- Incentivize models to consistently outperform the market, generating **incredible financial value** for both users and enterprise clients.
- **Attract skilled machine learning practitioners** to apply their expertise to sports prediction markets.
- Create an environment where machine learning practitioners can fiercely compete for rewards and **assert model dominance** over the industry.
- **Reworked dashboard** that details miner and model performance as well as generated value :moneyflying: 
- An **exciting new app** that we’ll be happy to share more about at a later date 👀 
- **Bonus**: You will be able to select which sport/league you want to predict for making requests and scoring siloed.

## :bongo_blob: What’s next?
We’ll first announce the **new GitHub repo** next week and run it on testnet so everyone has a chance to try it out, test your new models, see how the validators score your outputs etc. Then after a few days, we’ll merge to main *(increase reg for a couple hours)* and we’re live!

So don’t worry, you will have **plenty of time to adjust**! We want to make this evolution of our subnet is as seamless as possible for all parties.

It cannot be understated how excited and positive we are about the future of Sportstensor.
